('gradescope-ai', 'Gradescope', 'AI-assisted grading and assessment platform that accelerates feedback delivery for university instructors',
 E'Gradescope is an AI-assisted grading and assessment platform used by universities and colleges to dramatically reduce the time instructors and teaching assistants spend grading student work while improving the consistency and specificity of the feedback students receive. The platform supports grading of paper-based handwritten submissions (scanned), digital uploads, and programming assignments, making it applicable across disciplines from engineering and mathematics to humanities and social sciences.\n\nThe AI-assisted grading workflow groups similar student responses together automatically, allowing instructors to evaluate and comment on a cluster of similar answers at once rather than reviewing each submission individually. When an instructor marks a response correct and adds a comment, Gradescope applies the same mark and comment to all grouped responses that match - dramatically reducing redundant grading work on large class sizes. For university courses with 100+ students, this approach can reduce grading time by 50-70% according to instructor reports while producing more consistent marking than individual manual review.\n\nGradescope also provides rubric-based grading tools that allow instructors to define assessment criteria upfront and apply them consistently across the cohort. The analytics layer shows instructors where the class struggled - which questions had low average scores, which rubric criteria were most commonly missed - providing data for targeted in-class review. For programming assignments, Gradescope''s autograding infrastructure runs automated test suites against student submissions, providing instant feedback on correctness and freeing instructor time for the aspects of code review that require human judgment. Gradescope is now part of the Turnitin family and integrates with major learning management systems including Canvas, Blackboard, and Moodle.',
 'https://gradescope.com', 'https://gradescope.com',
 'freemium', true, 0, 4.5, 3400, false, false, false,
 ARRAY['education', 'teacher-tools', 'ai-assistants'],
 ARRAY['AI response grouping reduces redundant grading work on large class sizes by 50-70%', 'Consistent rubric-based marking improves fairness across large cohorts graded by multiple TAs', 'Analytics identify class-wide knowledge gaps for targeted instructional review', 'Autograding for programming assignments provides instant student feedback on correctness'],
 ARRAY['Most valuable for medium-to-large university classes - lower ROI for small seminars where personal grading is already fast', 'Initial rubric setup and workflow configuration takes time before the efficiency gains become visible', 'Paper submission workflow requires scanning infrastructure that smaller institutions may lack', 'Integration quality varies across LMS platforms - Moodle integration is less mature than Canvas'],
 ARRAY['University instructors grading large cohorts of handwritten or digital submissions faster with consistent rubrics', 'Computer science courses using autograding to provide instant correctness feedback on programming assignments', 'Teaching assistants grading collaboratively with consistent criteria across a team'],
 NOW()),

('kahoot-ai', 'Kahoot! AI', 'AI-powered quiz and game-based learning platform that generates course-aligned questions for engagement and formative assessment',
 E'Kahoot! is the game-based learning platform used by over 350 million users globally, and its AI features represent a meaningful evolution of the platform beyond manually-created quiz content. The Kahoot! AI question generator allows teachers and course creators to input a topic, paste source text, or specify a learning objective, and automatically generate a complete set of quiz questions with answer options - ready to run as a live game in class or assign as self-paced homework without manual question authorship.\n\nThe AI generation capability addresses one of the main friction points in Kahoot! adoption: creating quality question content takes time, and the platform''s game-based format is most effective when the question set is closely aligned to the specific material students are currently studying rather than generic subject questions. With AI generation, a teacher can create a 15-question formative assessment on the specific chapter assigned last night in under two minutes - low enough effort that it becomes a practical tool for daily or weekly lesson closers rather than a special event that requires advance preparation.\n\nKahoot! AI also includes a question improvement feature that reviews manually-written questions for clarity, answer option quality, and difficulty calibration, suggesting revisions that make the questions more pedagogically effective as formative assessment instruments. The Creator AI tool helps course creators on the Kahoot! platform produce structured learning courses with AI-generated content frameworks rather than starting from a blank structure. For businesses using Kahoot! for training and onboarding, the AI generation tools apply equally to corporate learning content as to academic curricula. The AI features are available on Kahoot! paid plans for teachers and businesses.',
 'https://kahoot.com', 'https://kahoot.com',
 'freemium', true, 8, 4.3, 6700, false, false, false,
 ARRAY['education', 'teacher-tools', 'e-learning'],
 ARRAY['AI question generation from topic input or source text creates formative assessments in under two minutes', 'Game-based format increases student engagement compared to traditional quiz formats', '350 million user base means extensive community-created question sets available as starting points', 'Works equally for academic classrooms and corporate training and onboarding programs'],
 ARRAY['Game format prioritises speed over depth - less suitable for complex analytical or open-ended assessment', 'AI question quality requires teacher review - generated questions can be too straightforward or contain errors', 'Full AI generation features require a paid plan - free plan has limitations on AI usage', 'Engagement peaks when used occasionally - frequent use can reduce the novelty effect that drives participation'],
 ARRAY['Teachers creating quick formative assessments aligned to the specific lesson content from that week', 'Corporate trainers building engagement into onboarding and compliance training programs', 'Course creators on the Kahoot! platform generating structured course content frameworks with AI assistance'],
