('nearpod-ai', 'Nearpod AI', 'AI-powered interactive lesson platform that generates engaging, standards-aligned classroom presentations',
 E'Nearpod is an interactive lesson and assessment platform used by K-12 teachers to create and deliver lessons that include student participation tools - polls, open-ended questions, quizzes, virtual reality experiences, and collaborative boards - embedded directly in the lesson flow rather than as separate tools. The Nearpod AI features, launched progressively across the platform, use AI to generate complete interactive lesson drafts from a topic and grade level input, reducing the time a teacher spends building an engaging lesson from hours to minutes.\n\nThe AI lesson generation outputs a structured Nearpod presentation with slides, embedded knowledge checks, discussion prompts, and formative assessment questions already integrated into the lesson flow - not a passive slide deck that a teacher then needs to retrofit with interactivity. For teachers who are new to the platform or who are building lessons in subjects outside their deepest expertise, the AI-generated structure provides a sound pedagogical starting point that can be customised rather than a blank canvas. The generated content aligns to Common Core and state standards when a grade level and subject are specified.\n\nNearpod''s student-facing interactivity is the platform''s core differentiator from general AI lesson generators. Students participate in real time during live teacher-led sessions or work through lessons at their own pace in student-paced mode. The teacher dashboard shows individual student responses as they are submitted, allowing the teacher to adjust the lesson pace and address misconceptions in real time based on actual class data rather than guessing at understanding levels. For schools and districts that have adopted Nearpod as a core classroom technology, the AI generation features meaningfully reduce the planning time required to keep lesson content fresh and interactive without sacrificing the participation elements that drive the platform''s engagement value.',
 'https://nearpod.com', 'https://nearpod.com',
 'freemium', true, 18, 4.3, 2900, false, false, false,
 ARRAY['education', 'teacher-tools', 'e-learning'],
 ARRAY['AI generates complete interactive lessons with embedded polls, quizzes, and discussion prompts - not just slide content', 'Real-time student response dashboard allows teachers to adjust pacing based on actual class comprehension', 'Standards alignment for Common Core and state standards built into AI generation workflow', 'Student-paced mode allows asynchronous delivery for absent students or flipped classroom models'],
 ARRAY['Full AI generation and advanced features require a paid school or district plan', 'AI-generated lesson content requires teacher review for accuracy and local curriculum alignment', 'Most valuable when students are engaged through school-issued devices - BYOD implementation can be inconsistent', 'Content depth on highly specialised topics may require significant manual customisation beyond the AI draft'],
