('edpuzzle-ai', 'Edpuzzle AI', 'AI-powered video lesson platform that embeds questions and comprehension checks into educational videos',
 E'Edpuzzle is a video-based learning platform that allows teachers to take any educational video - from YouTube, Khan Academy, National Geographic, TED-Ed, or any other source - and embed interactive questions, audio notes, and comprehension checks directly into the video timeline. Students cannot skip past embedded questions, ensuring active engagement with the video content rather than passive watching. The Edpuzzle AI features automate the most time-consuming part of this workflow: question creation.\n\nThe AI question generation analyses video content and automatically suggests relevant comprehension and analysis questions at appropriate timestamps throughout the video. For a 10-minute science documentary, Edpuzzle AI might generate eight questions embedded at the moments in the video where the key concepts are introduced, with a mix of multiple choice, true/false, and short answer formats. The teacher reviews, adjusts, and selects from the AI suggestions rather than writing questions from scratch - reducing the lesson preparation time while maintaining teacher control over the specific comprehension points the lesson is assessing.\n\nEdpuzzle also provides a library of pre-made video lessons created by other teachers across all subjects and grade levels, which can be assigned directly or used as a starting point with customisation. The teacher dashboard tracks individual student completion, time spent, and question performance, providing the data teachers need to identify students who are struggling with the video content before the next class session. For teachers implementing flipped classroom models where students watch instructional videos at home before class discussion, Edpuzzle''s accountability and comprehension tracking makes the model operationally practical rather than reliant on students self-reporting their preparation. The platform is used by over 20 million educators globally and supports content delivery in over 60 languages.',
 'https://edpuzzle.com', 'https://edpuzzle.com',
 'freemium', true, 0, 4.4, 4100, false, false, false,
 ARRAY['education', 'teacher-tools', 'e-learning'],
 ARRAY['AI question generation suggests comprehension checks at relevant video timestamps automatically', 'Works with any YouTube, Khan Academy, or uploaded video - no proprietary content library required', 'Student skip prevention ensures active video engagement rather than passive playback', 'Comprehension tracking dashboard identifies struggling students before the next class session'],
 ARRAY['AI question suggestions require teacher review - quality varies by video type and subject complexity', 'Video-centric format is less suitable for subjects where reading or hands-on practice is the primary learning mode', 'Free plan limits the number of videos that can be assigned per teacher per month', 'Embedded question format works best for informational and documentary video types - less effective for demonstration or tutorial videos'],
 ARRAY['Teachers implementing flipped classroom models who need comprehension accountability on assigned video homework', 'K-12 teachers embedding formative assessment into video-based lesson content without manual question authorship', 'Schools tracking student video engagement and comprehension performance at the individual student level'],
